# Tailwind CSS & Styling System

## The Navigator Color System

### Theme Colors (use these via Tailwind or CSS variables)

| Color | Tailwind | CSS Variable | Usage |
|-------|----------|--------------|-------|
| Navigator (Coral) | `navigator-500` | `--navigator` | Primary accent, signature |
| Compass (Gold) | `compass-500` | `--compass` | CTAs, guidance |
| Horizon (Teal) | `horizon-500` | `--horizon` | Links, exploration |
| Pathfinder (Indigo) | `pathfinder-500` | `--pathfinder` | Code, technical |
| Growth (Green) | `growth` | `--growth` | Success, achievements |
| Canvas | `canvas-50` to `canvas-300` | `--canvas-*` | Backgrounds |
| Ink | `ink-100` to `ink-700` | `--ink-*` | Text |
| Cosmos | `cosmos-50` to `cosmos-400` | N/A | Dark mode backgrounds |

### Using CSS Variables in Inline Styles

```jsx
// ✅ Correct: Use rgb() with CSS variable
style={{ color: 'rgb(var(--navigator))' }}
style={{ backgroundColor: 'rgba(var(--navigator), 0.1)' }}
style={{ borderColor: 'rgb(var(--border-primary))' }}

// ❌ Wrong: Don't use hex colors inline
style={{ color: '#FF6B4A' }}
```

### Using CSS Variables in Tailwind Classes

```jsx
// ✅ Correct: Use bracket notation
className="text-[rgb(var(--navigator))]"
className="bg-[rgba(var(--navigator),0.1)]"
className="border-[rgb(var(--border-primary))]"

// Or use Tailwind theme colors
className="text-navigator-500"
className="bg-compass-400"
```

